                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Solo guide to PoV is following.<br />At zone in put on undead invis and follow straight north from zone in to the castle. Plenty of undead in forest to make life miserable.  Take off undead invis and put on regular invis.  Follow up the stairs to the top of the ramp.  You are looking over the wastelands.  While invis, con some of the golems below you in the wastelands and you will notice that some can see thru invis and some cant.  Make sure you at least have run 3, J boots or Sow.  While invis run off top of ramp and head east to where mtn wall is, avoiding the golems and spiders there....Once at wall follow north to north east corner where there is the best necro camp in the place.  <br /><br />Get pet set up, buff it and get ready for great exp.<br />Note:  pull ONLY golems and crawlers as spiders are NONSNARABLE.. <br /><br />Get at max distance from golem and snare.  If you are resisted, and you will be, you will need all the distance you can get between you and mob as they are very fast and 2-3 hits can easily take ya out.  If resisted just run alongside the mountain north to south and resnare.  Once snared, mobs are toast, but due to such high hitpoints you will have to re-snare several times.  <br /><br />After snare, I funeral pyre (if you have it) dark plaque, pyrocuror, and splurt.  I reapply FP when needed and DOT lifetap if low on hp or i get hit. I sic pet after first funeralpyre has stuck.  Merely aggro kite along the mountain side, back and forth while your pet carves it's name in the mobs back.<br /><br />Do NOT try to have pet tank as it will get wasted rather quickly.  If pet gains aggro, pull it off fast.<br /><br />Also if you get an add, you best get out of there quickly, unless both are snared and you have a ton of mana.  AGAIN, if you pull a spider(non-snareable) you can FD or run to zone.  To escape the fastest and easiest...just run south alongside the easternwall and off the wastelands cliff.  DmF is always on for me. From my exp, the mobs dont chase you off the cliff, but I have never stuck around to find out.<br /><br />Good Luck</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="bottom"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> "To crush your enemies, see them run before you and to hear the lamentation of the women"</span></font></td>
