                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> PoV: I find the best camp that is to be had in the zone for a necro and friends is what is called OC (Outter Caves) camp. If you run due west as you zone in you will hit water and see a mouth of a cave. Set up on the hill.<br /><br />I can solo these mobs no problem, but it isn't nearly as fun nor profitable xp wise solo. Sure i get 6 percent per kill of AAXP, but if can kite 4 at a time you are making that much better xp.<br /><br />Your best bet for a group is a sower, and then any of the following. Beastlords, Mage, Wizzie, or someone with DC.<br /><br />The tactics are easy. The necro is the puller for this camp, why so you can control aggro. Get your self a sow, get a pet a sow, park pet and run to tunnel. Their is 1 static spawn in that tunnel, and 2 wanders through it. I snare one (63 snare is the truth here), funeral pyre it, and cast 1-3 level4 fears on it before it gets back to camp. You can do this with just level 4 fears for aggro. Then challenege anyone to take aggro from you. Once that one is done, run in tunnel, near end of tunnel you see a rock on left (if you are a gnome like you should be) you can run a top this rock and peer into open cave. From the rock you will not get aggro and you can cast on mobs from there. What i do since i hate FD'in splitting because it is a waste of xp time. I snare the static GOLEM spawn and immdiately target the razorfiend behind rock on left, run back down tunnel and snare fiend. This means i have two mobs on me. I tell group to please assist pet. MAKE SURE to get atleast two level 4 fears on these mobs to establish aggro before you engage pet and make sure group knows to wait for pet. While one group is working on mob pet is on (you occasionaly casting level 4 fear for aggro) i will drop dots on other mob not being hit.<br /><br />Once you get good at this you can do 4-5 at a time with no problems, just needs a good sense of timing.<br /><br />If late at night, and IC (Inner Caves) is not camped and i am able to pull from it i will make 1 aaxp point in 45 minutes. This is as best as it gets in my opinion, why because you are in total y control of this group, the pulling, everything and you can just keep going and going if you are diligent. I have earned 12 aa's in a night/morning there no problem.<br /><br />Hope this helps, we are gods of this camp.<br /><br />Lich Shadwick of Xev<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378602" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378602</a><br />Proud member of Debonair<br /><a href="http://www.eqdebonair.com" target="_blank">www.eqdebonair.com</a><br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
